Item Description 1990 Fender American Stratocaster Plus Ultra in very good condition. The front has light pick marks next to the neck pickup, a light scratch next to the middle pickup, a light ding close to the scratch and a finish blemish by the output jack. The blemish appears to be below the finish. The back has a moderate amount of light scratches. Classic Sunburst finish on the lightly figured body with a white pickguard and chrome hardware. The guitar has a nice action and the thin profile maple neck with an ebony fretboard has a very good feel. The medium jumbo frets are in very good condition with only light playwear.The Fender Lace Sensor pickups (blue/gold/red) have a nice tone and good output. The bridge position is a humbucker made from 2 Fender Lace Sensor Reds. This pickup has a lot of output. The electronics are a 5-way toggle switch, TBX tone circuit and a three position(front coil/series/rear coil) switch for the bridge pickup. The guitar is equipped with a roller nut, locking tuners a two point tremolo with solid block saddles and a Trem-setter tremolo stabilizer. This is a really nice looking, sounding and playing guitar.Includes a gig bag and tremolo arm. Serial Number: E972981 Weight: 7 lbs. 12 oz.
